Empirical evidence for our reranking objective.
Fig. 2 summarizes the overall retrieval-stage results: ProGRank consistently reduces both Poison Hit Rate and Poison Recall Rate relative to the undefended ranking, with the strongest effect on HotpotQA. On NQ and MS MARCO, the Top-50 Poison Hit Rate is also reduced to around 30%. This trend is reflected in Fig. 4, where poisoned passages show almost no upward rank shift but much larger downward shifts than clean passages. Fig. 3 further shows that poisoned passages tend to receive larger penalties and gate values, so stronger correction is applied in the decision-critical high-score region. Fig. 5 shows that the full gated objective performs best overall, and that removing causes a larger degradation than removing . Taken together, these results provide empirical evidence that the proposed reranking objective helps suppress poisoned passages while preserving its focus on the high-score region. Experimental details are provided in Sec. 4.1.
